text:
The exploration that I sent through last night is interesting, but at the moment I cannot see it working well from an experience and visual point of view.
At this time the drawer idea still seems to make the most sense to me. I will be at the office at around 11 but have adidas meetings from then on.
Will reconnect with you all in between or afterwards
okay cool - yeah let’s plan on reconnecting any time we all have a couple minutes
sorry josh, let’s nix standup today
i’ll come chat with folks individually
<@U0EL0GLEL>: can you try to access the git repo again and let me know if it all works?
did you figure out what happened?

i responded to the email with a screen cap of what im seeing. I do see one empty repo now. appears to be a place for us to commit to. Not sure if that is the only intention here? I have figured out how to create activities and deploy them into IS tho. And I have played with some of these samples. The tcp network one worked great, able to setup a listener in an IS activity that will listen for TCP ping over the network. I couldnt get the image viewer to work, it the file uploader part would not respond. and the video player appeared to work but didnt support a youtube video source which might be just part of how it works
re: hinge, root cause undetermined. general fuckery probably

<@U0EL0GLEL>: thanks for the update and for the response to Myles. My guess is that’s all he set up for us to be able to commit to, but we’ll see what he says. also sounds good about getting those samples to work. i’ll look to <@U02E3CRMA> to point you in the right direction for next steps
I’m about to disappear for a while to stuff the Trello board, among other things. I’ll ping you when it’s ready.
